    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S (996.2) features the iconic wide-body architecture and integrated all-wheel-drive system. Powered by a 3.6L M96 flat-six paired with a crisp G96 6-speed manual transaxle, the powertrain utilizes VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing and lift. The chassis is equipped with Turbo-spec suspension geometry and 'Big Red' four-piston monobloc calipers for superior thermal management. Maintenance is current, featuring an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a replaced Rear Main Seal (RMS) to ensure the integrity of the rotating assembly. The viscous clutch AWD system delivers precise torque vectoring, providing exceptional mechanical grip through the apex. A mechanically sound example with a documented service history and robust compression across all cylinders.",
